WEBVTT

00:02.045 --> 00:05.135
[T. Rex's "Get It On
[Bang a Gong]"]

00:05.179 --> 00:07.659
♪

00:07.703 --> 00:09.574
- ♪ Well,
you're dirty and sweet ♪

00:09.618 --> 00:11.620
♪ Clad in black,
don't look back ♪

00:11.663 --> 00:14.057
♪ And I love you

00:14.101 --> 00:17.408
♪ You're dirty and sweet,
oh, yeah ♪

00:17.452 --> 00:19.367
♪

00:19.410 --> 00:21.325
♪ Well,
you're slim and you're weak ♪

00:21.369 --> 00:25.677
♪ You've got the teeth
of the hydra upon you ♪

00:25.721 --> 00:28.158
♪ You're dirty sweet
and you're my girl ♪

00:28.202 --> 00:29.333
- First I saw the name

00:29.377 --> 00:31.335
and I thought it was
a coincidence.

00:31.379 --> 00:34.512
Then I saw the order
and I knew it was you.

00:34.556 --> 00:35.513
How you doing, Remy?

00:35.557 --> 00:36.514
- Good, Sal.
Good.

00:36.558 --> 00:37.646
- You in town on business?

00:37.689 --> 00:39.474
- Yeah, pretty much.

00:39.517 --> 00:40.518
- Well, don't be a stranger.

00:40.562 --> 00:41.693
We missed you around here.

00:41.737 --> 00:43.304
That'll be $26.80.

00:43.347 --> 00:44.696
♪

00:44.740 --> 00:46.524
- Keep the change.
- ♪ And you're my girl

00:46.568 --> 00:48.265
- Maybe get yourself a haircut.

00:48.309 --> 00:49.527
♪

00:49.571 --> 00:51.529
- ♪ Get it on

00:51.573 --> 00:53.488
♪ Bang a gong, get it on

00:53.531 --> 00:55.620
- And there he is,
the man himself!

00:55.664 --> 00:57.100
- How you doing, Georgie?

00:57.144 --> 00:59.624
- Oh, come on.
You went to Napoli's?

00:59.668 --> 01:01.148
- Pastrami sandwich for you.

01:01.191 --> 01:02.366
Cannolis for the wife.
- [laughs]

01:02.410 --> 01:03.759
You remembered.
Thank you.

01:03.802 --> 01:05.717
Hey, you got any more bags
in the car?

01:05.761 --> 01:07.197
- Nah,
I had everything shipped.

01:07.241 --> 01:08.677
Hey, listen.

01:08.720 --> 01:09.678
Is Joey still doing his car
wash thing in the garage?

01:09.721 --> 01:11.158
- Yeah, Tuesdays and Thursdays.

01:11.201 --> 01:12.333
- Have him do it for me,
would you?

01:12.376 --> 01:13.682
- Mm-hmm.

01:13.725 --> 01:14.552
- I just got it out of storage
after four years

01:14.596 --> 01:16.511
and it could use some love.

01:16.554 --> 01:18.208
- [laughing]
You got it.

01:18.252 --> 01:19.775
Hey, Remy.

01:19.818 --> 01:21.907
Welcome back.
- ♪ Get it on

01:21.951 --> 01:23.213
- It's good to be home,
Georgie.

01:23.257 --> 01:25.259
- Hm.
- ♪ Get it on

01:25.302 --> 01:26.564
- It's good to be home.

01:26.608 --> 01:29.350
♪

01:33.441 --> 01:36.444
[soft dark music]

01:36.792 --> 01:43.799
♪

02:01.730 --> 02:03.775
- You're shaking.
- I can't help it.

02:03.819 --> 02:05.473
I'm so scared.
I'm not sure if--

02:05.516 --> 02:07.779
- Lillie, we talked about this.

02:07.823 --> 02:09.607
I already did my part.

02:09.651 --> 02:11.435
It's the only way.

02:11.479 --> 02:15.744
♪

02:15.787 --> 02:17.659
This is for us.

02:17.702 --> 02:19.791
♪

02:19.835 --> 02:21.228
I love you.

02:21.271 --> 02:23.534
Go wait in the car.

02:23.578 --> 02:30.541
♪

02:30.585 --> 02:33.544
[suspenseful music]

02:33.588 --> 02:40.595
♪

03:15.282 --> 03:18.241
[suspenseful music crescendos]

03:18.285 --> 03:25.248
♪

03:33.822 --> 03:35.780
- New York City field office.

03:35.824 --> 03:38.696
Worked with Violent Crimes out
of Philly for six years.

03:38.740 --> 03:41.003
- His last job was the
Vegas Fugitive Task Force.

03:41.046 --> 03:42.874
- Yeah, I called him and they
said he's a straight shooter

03:42.918 --> 03:43.962
and knows his stuff.
- Hm.

03:44.006 --> 03:45.877
- He's been with the bureau
for...

03:45.921 --> 03:47.531
looks like 23 years.

03:47.575 --> 03:48.619
Wow.

03:48.663 --> 03:50.795
Graduated top of his class.

03:50.839 --> 03:52.057
- Morning, everyone.
How you doing?

03:52.101 --> 03:53.494
I'm Remy Scott, your new boss.

03:53.537 --> 03:55.322
And I want you to know
I'm never usually this late.

03:55.365 --> 03:56.932
Today is the exception.

03:56.975 --> 03:57.976
- How you doing?
I'm Ivan.

03:58.020 --> 04:00.327
- Ortiz,
heard you were a badass.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.589
- Hana.
- Gibson.

04:01.632 --> 04:02.938
The brains of the operation.

04:02.981 --> 04:04.722
- Mm-hmm.
Kristin Gaines.

04:04.766 --> 04:05.984
- Yeah,
from the Miami field office.

04:06.028 --> 04:08.291
Delgado says good things.

04:08.335 --> 04:10.685
Did Agent Barnes take
her maternity leave?

04:10.728 --> 04:11.947
- She did.

04:11.990 --> 04:14.036
- Well, I look forward
to meeting her too.

04:14.079 --> 04:17.561
- So here's the thing.

04:17.605 --> 04:18.736
I had big plans
for us this morning.

04:18.780 --> 04:19.955
Break bread,
get to know each other

04:19.998 --> 04:22.000
over some of the best bagels
in the city,

04:22.044 --> 04:23.654
but it looks like
we're diving right in.

04:23.698 --> 04:24.742
I heard Scarsdale?

04:24.786 --> 04:25.874
- Correct.

04:25.917 --> 04:27.745
It's a double homicide
home invasion.

04:27.789 --> 04:30.922
The victims are Matt Jones,
a big-time hedge fund manager

04:30.966 --> 04:32.794
and his wife, Kay,
a corporate attorney.

04:32.837 --> 04:34.404
- Well, I get
that they're high-profile,

04:34.448 --> 04:35.623
but why isn't homicide on this?

04:35.666 --> 04:36.624
- Their daughter's missing.

04:36.667 --> 04:37.712
They think she was kidnapped.

04:37.755 --> 04:39.888
- Kidnapped?
Can I see that?

04:39.931 --> 04:41.977
- Her name's Lillie.
17-year-old junior

04:42.020 --> 04:44.936
at a private school in Rye.

04:44.980 --> 04:46.677
- Any ransom demand?
- No.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.766
- Amber Alert went out
40 minutes ago.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.333
♪

04:50.377 --> 04:51.900
- [sighs]
All right, then let's roll.

04:51.943 --> 04:54.598
Isobel said two Tahoes, right?
- That's right.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.339
- You two go together.
I'll ride with Hana.

04:56.383 --> 04:57.819
And this time of day,
take the Hutch.

04:57.862 --> 05:00.604
Post road will be a nightmare.

05:00.648 --> 05:02.693
- I'll drive.

05:02.737 --> 05:05.696
[suspenseful dramatic music]

05:05.740 --> 05:09.439
♪

05:09.483 --> 05:11.833
- You okay?
- Mm.

05:11.876 --> 05:14.879
Yeah,
just kind of a late night.

05:14.923 --> 05:17.969
- Mm.
- Mm.

05:18.013 --> 05:19.971
♪

05:20.015 --> 05:22.757
Always hated that picture.

05:22.800 --> 05:26.935
♪

05:26.978 --> 05:28.458
- Dad never knew what hit him.

05:28.502 --> 05:30.504
Her wounds are defensive,
though.

05:30.547 --> 05:32.375
Probably tried to run.

05:32.419 --> 05:33.768
Didn't make it.

05:33.811 --> 05:35.683
- She must have been terrified.

05:35.726 --> 05:37.772
Sound asleep in her own bed
and then...

05:37.815 --> 05:39.687
- Cover them up, please.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.471
♪

05:41.515 --> 05:42.733
- I can't let you upstairs
right now.

05:42.777 --> 05:43.952
- I need to see her.
- I understand.

05:43.995 --> 05:45.562
- Please, she's my sister.
- I'm so sorry.

05:45.606 --> 05:47.085
- Is it her?
Are they dead?

05:47.129 --> 05:48.783
- This is Martha.
This is Mrs. Jones' sister.

05:48.826 --> 05:50.611
- I have to see her.
- I wanna see my Kay.

05:50.654 --> 05:52.395
- Martha,
I'm Special Agent Remy Scott

05:52.439 --> 05:54.484
and this is Agent Gibson.

05:54.528 --> 05:56.181
I don't think
that's a good idea right now.

05:56.225 --> 05:58.183
- What did he do to her?

05:58.227 --> 05:59.837
Where did he take Lillie?

05:59.881 --> 06:01.143
- Who?

06:01.186 --> 06:02.579
- Jeremy Hamm.

06:02.623 --> 06:05.147
He's the one who did this.

06:05.190 --> 06:06.453
- I know you're upset,

06:06.496 --> 06:07.845
but I need you to take
a deep breath.

06:07.889 --> 06:09.412
Can you do that for me?

06:09.456 --> 06:11.022
That's it.
Just breathe.

06:11.066 --> 06:12.372
Here, why don't you sit down?

06:14.591 --> 06:16.680
Can I get you a glass of water
or anything?

06:16.724 --> 06:18.552
- No.

06:19.857 --> 06:22.033
- Tell me all about Jeremy.

06:22.077 --> 06:23.948
- [sighs]

06:23.992 --> 06:26.037
He's a loser and a freak.

06:26.081 --> 06:27.517
Okay?

06:27.561 --> 06:29.171
He was trying to date Lillie

06:29.214 --> 06:30.868
and Matt and Kay
didn't approve.

06:30.912 --> 06:32.479
And I don't blame them.

06:32.522 --> 06:35.438
- Did he know Lillie
from school?

06:35.482 --> 06:37.658
- I don't know.

06:37.701 --> 06:39.790
My sister and Matt are
very private.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.879
They don't like talking about
their problems.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.577
[somber music]

06:43.620 --> 06:47.972
Um, all Kay told me is
this boy is trouble.

06:48.016 --> 06:50.453
Lillie thinks she's in love
with him, and, um,

06:50.497 --> 06:52.107
and they're putting a stop
to it right away.

06:52.150 --> 06:54.501
They told her that she couldn't
see him anymore.

06:54.544 --> 06:57.460
♪

06:57.504 --> 06:59.157
- Is this him?

06:59.201 --> 07:00.811
- [cries]
Yes.

07:00.855 --> 07:03.074
Yes, that's the little bastard.

07:03.118 --> 07:06.469
Oh, my God, I can't believe
this is happening.

07:06.513 --> 07:08.515
- It's okay.

07:08.558 --> 07:09.907
- [cries]
- Martha.

07:09.951 --> 07:12.083
Thank you so much.
You've been very helpful.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.520
♪

07:13.563 --> 07:16.697
- Martha,
let's get you some water, okay?

07:16.740 --> 07:21.223
♪

07:21.266 --> 07:22.529
- Does he have a record?

07:22.572 --> 07:23.921
- Two charges as a juvenile,

07:23.965 --> 07:26.620
then six months in county
for drug possession at 19.

07:26.663 --> 07:28.143
His father's deceased.

07:28.186 --> 07:30.972
His mother's in Secaucus,
which is also his last known.

07:31.015 --> 07:33.191
- Secaucus is a long way
from Scarsdale.

07:33.235 --> 07:34.889
- Literally and figuratively.

07:34.932 --> 07:37.021
- I don't think we're dealing
with a kidnapping here.

07:37.065 --> 07:38.240
- Why is that?

07:38.283 --> 07:39.763
- No forced entry
on the windows and doors

07:39.807 --> 07:41.635
and someone took the batteries
out of the Ring cameras.

07:41.678 --> 07:43.680
- You check Lillie's bedroom?
- I did.

07:43.724 --> 07:45.595
Bed's made and toiletries gone
from the bathroom.

07:45.639 --> 07:46.988
If she fought him,
it wasn't in there.

07:47.031 --> 07:48.685
- You think she went willingly?

07:48.729 --> 07:51.514
- Either that or she helped.

07:51.558 --> 07:52.776
- Kill her own parents?

07:52.820 --> 07:54.778
- Two kids in love caught
in a bad romance,

07:54.822 --> 07:56.519
parents cut off
the relationship?

07:56.563 --> 07:57.607
It's happened before.

07:57.651 --> 07:59.783
- Not at my high school.
- [sighs]

07:59.827 --> 08:02.307
Jeremy have a car registration?
- Yeah.

08:02.351 --> 08:04.309
1994 Camry.

08:04.353 --> 08:05.833
- BOLO that and let's split up.

08:05.876 --> 08:07.138
Lillie's school
and Jeremy's mom.

08:07.182 --> 08:08.836
Let's roll.

08:08.879 --> 08:14.798
♪

08:14.842 --> 08:17.192
[knock on door]
Mrs. Hamm?

08:17.235 --> 08:20.325
FBI, we need to talk!

08:20.369 --> 08:21.805
Hello?

08:21.849 --> 08:24.634
- TV's on inside.
No movement.

08:24.678 --> 08:30.597
♪

08:30.640 --> 08:32.816
[tense music]

08:32.860 --> 08:36.559
-...my favorite, the
Angel Love double halo ring.

08:36.603 --> 08:38.692
- Oh!
- Is that gorgeous or what?

08:38.735 --> 08:41.999
- Oh, it is just beautiful.
I wear it all the time.

08:42.043 --> 08:45.263
[indistinct chatter on TV]

08:45.307 --> 08:46.874
- We have a body
in the kitchen.

08:46.917 --> 08:51.661
♪

08:51.705 --> 08:52.836
- [coughs]
Clear.

08:52.880 --> 08:54.316
- Ortiz.

08:54.359 --> 08:57.275
♪

08:57.319 --> 08:58.668
Between the stench
and the rigor,

08:58.712 --> 09:00.888
she's been dead
at least 24 hours.

09:00.931 --> 09:03.630
Jeremy probably snuck up
on her from behind.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.327
- He kills her first and then
he goes over to Lillie's

09:05.370 --> 09:07.024
and takes care of her parents.

09:07.068 --> 09:08.112
- Yeah,
assuming she didn't approve

09:08.156 --> 09:10.680
of their relationship either.

09:10.724 --> 09:12.595
- At least maybe they're done
killing for now.

09:12.639 --> 09:14.597
[soft suspenseful music]

09:14.641 --> 09:17.208
- But we still don't know
where they are.

09:17.252 --> 09:19.602
Call local homicide and offer
up our ERT.

09:19.646 --> 09:22.910
I'm pulling Jersey State Police
into this search.

09:22.953 --> 09:29.960
♪

09:31.179 --> 09:32.833
- You okay?

09:32.876 --> 09:34.878
- [sighs]
I think so.

09:34.922 --> 09:36.837
♪

09:36.880 --> 09:37.925
You?

09:37.968 --> 09:39.709
♪

09:39.753 --> 09:42.843
- The worst part is over.

09:42.886 --> 09:46.629
And I don't wanna think about
anything now except us.

09:46.673 --> 09:48.065
♪

09:48.109 --> 09:49.414
[laughs]

09:49.458 --> 09:56.596
♪

09:58.336 --> 10:00.208
- Want me to put this on?

10:00.251 --> 10:02.732
♪

10:02.776 --> 10:04.038
[laughs]

10:04.081 --> 10:06.170
Now you're the one
who's shaking.

10:06.214 --> 10:09.086
Are you nervous?

10:09.130 --> 10:11.262
- No.
- Good.

10:11.306 --> 10:12.786
- Because I wouldn't want
my first time

10:12.829 --> 10:14.048
to be with anyone else.

10:14.091 --> 10:21.098
♪

10:25.755 --> 10:27.975
[knock at door]

10:28.018 --> 10:29.672
- Go hide in the bathroom.

10:29.716 --> 10:36.723
♪

10:37.419 --> 10:39.029
- Port Authority has
the bridges and tunnels.

10:39.073 --> 10:40.422
MTA are on the trains.

10:40.465 --> 10:41.858
But if they're not headed back
to New York,

10:41.902 --> 10:44.774
I want this highways covered
tight as a gnat's ass.

10:44.818 --> 10:45.775
Let's move.

10:45.819 --> 10:47.429
- We're on it.
- All right.

10:47.472 --> 10:48.996
- Anything
from Lillie's school?

10:49.039 --> 10:49.997
- They don't know Jeremy.

10:50.040 --> 10:51.346
Got an earful on Lillie though.

10:51.389 --> 10:52.782
She's been going there
since the seventh grade.

10:52.826 --> 10:54.436
Straight A student
until six months ago.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.307
- Her grades started dropping,
she started losing weight,

10:56.351 --> 10:57.352
and then missing days
at school.

10:57.395 --> 10:58.832
- They kick her out?
- No.

10:58.875 --> 11:00.485
Her parents called it
a "family emergency."

11:00.529 --> 11:02.139
Her father was on the board.
A huge donor.

11:02.183 --> 11:03.445
So they looked the other way.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.968
- It's good to be the king.

11:05.012 --> 11:06.796
- The "family emergency" was
probably Jeremy.

11:06.840 --> 11:08.189
They didn't want people to know
that their daughter was

11:08.232 --> 11:09.930
hanging out
with a 22-year-old ex-con

11:09.973 --> 11:11.758
with a history of drug abuse.

11:11.801 --> 11:13.324
- BOLO got a hit
on Jeremy's Camry

11:13.368 --> 11:14.978
outside a motel in Yonkers.

11:15.022 --> 11:16.719
♪

11:16.763 --> 11:19.809
- We knocked
and no one answered.

11:19.853 --> 11:22.116
Busted the door and found this.

11:22.159 --> 11:24.466
[indistinct radio chatter]

11:24.509 --> 11:26.903
- Any ID?
- No.

11:26.947 --> 11:28.731
Wallet and phone are missing.

11:28.775 --> 11:31.168
- He's still warm.
It just happened.

11:31.212 --> 11:33.170
- Camry's outside.
So how'd they get away?

11:33.214 --> 11:34.389
Anything on the radio?

11:34.432 --> 11:38.132
- Not so far,
but all units are looking.

11:38.175 --> 11:39.786
- I got
the security cam footage

11:39.829 --> 11:41.135
from the manager's office.

11:41.178 --> 11:43.354
It's not the best quality,
but the angle's good.

11:43.398 --> 11:45.922
♪

11:45.966 --> 11:47.968
- Our young lovers are
definitely working together.

11:48.011 --> 11:49.012
- Forget young lovers.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.361
These two
are on a killing spree.

11:50.405 --> 11:53.016
We got four dead bodies
in less than 24 hours.

11:53.060 --> 11:55.062
And our unidentified DOA
in there isn't one

11:55.105 --> 11:57.368
of their parents, so what
the hell's going on here?

11:57.412 --> 11:58.761
- Well,
if that is the victim's car,

11:58.805 --> 12:00.328
he won't be unidentified
for long.

12:00.371 --> 12:02.852
Gimme a second.

12:02.896 --> 12:04.767
The car belongs to David Ryan.

12:04.811 --> 12:06.943
83 99th Street in Tarrytown.

12:06.987 --> 12:08.423
- Dave "the Rhino" Ryan.

12:08.466 --> 12:09.554
He's a private investigator.

12:09.598 --> 12:11.382
And it looks like
he has a partner.

12:11.426 --> 12:12.993
- Get his partner down here.

12:13.036 --> 12:16.083
♪

12:20.957 --> 12:22.437
- Yeah, that's her.
That's Lillie.

12:22.480 --> 12:23.873
I remember her from a photo

12:23.917 --> 12:26.789
her parents brought
in two weeks ago.

12:26.833 --> 12:28.530
- The Joneses hired
your PI firm?

12:28.573 --> 12:30.837
- Yeah.
It was Dave's case.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.839
But I was there
for the intake interview.

12:32.882 --> 12:34.449
- They said Lillie had
addiction issues

12:34.492 --> 12:36.364
and they'd sent her to this
rehab clinic in Brooklyn.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.409
Intentions, it was called.

12:38.453 --> 12:39.889
They were convinced
something bad was going on

12:39.933 --> 12:41.630
and they wanted us
to take a look at it.

12:41.673 --> 12:44.372
- What did they mean
by "something bad"?

12:44.415 --> 12:46.374
- It wasn't specific.
It was just--

12:46.417 --> 12:47.636
she wasn't getting better

12:47.679 --> 12:49.246
and they couldn't get
a straight answer

12:49.290 --> 12:50.465
out of anyone.

12:50.508 --> 12:51.814
And then one night
Lillie comes home

12:51.858 --> 12:53.598
and she's all disoriented
and drugged out,

12:53.642 --> 12:54.817
and that was that.

12:54.861 --> 12:57.515
They yanked her out
and gave us a call.

12:57.559 --> 12:59.779
- You know this man?
Jeremy Hamm?

12:59.822 --> 13:01.606
- No.
Who's he?

13:01.650 --> 13:02.999
- Lillie's boyfriend.

13:03.043 --> 13:05.393
We think he killed the Joneses,
his own mother,

13:05.436 --> 13:07.743
and now possibly your partner
with Lillie helping.

13:07.787 --> 13:10.267
- No, Dave was trying
to help Lillie.

13:10.311 --> 13:12.661
Why would she wanna hurt him?

13:12.704 --> 13:14.010
- Do you have Dave's case file?

13:14.054 --> 13:16.534
- Yeah, back at the office.
- We'll need a copy.

13:16.578 --> 13:18.319
You two head down
to Intentions Rehab.

13:18.362 --> 13:19.668
See what you can dig up.

13:19.711 --> 13:20.887
- Sure.

13:20.930 --> 13:25.282
- You know, I don't get it.

13:25.326 --> 13:28.068
Most of the time we deal
with what, deadbeat dads

13:28.111 --> 13:31.723
and cheating spouses,
but now this?

13:31.767 --> 13:33.987
Dave has two kids.

13:34.030 --> 13:38.078
What am I supposed
to tell them?

13:38.121 --> 13:41.516
- Tell 'em
we're gonna find who did this.

13:41.559 --> 13:44.040
And we're gonna make 'em pay.

13:44.084 --> 13:46.564
[dramatic music]

13:46.608 --> 13:48.610
♪

13:48.653 --> 13:51.395
- Yes,
Lillie was a patient here.

13:51.439 --> 13:53.049
Why?
- She's missing.

13:53.093 --> 13:54.572
We think she might be
in danger.

13:54.616 --> 13:57.097
- Oh, my God.
Lillie? What happened?

13:57.140 --> 13:59.316
- Her parents recently hired
a private investigator.

13:59.360 --> 14:00.970
They were concerned
that something bad had happened

14:01.014 --> 14:02.058
to her here.

14:02.102 --> 14:03.930
Do you know anything
about that?

14:03.973 --> 14:07.368
- Something bad
did happen here.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.630
Jeremy.

14:08.673 --> 14:10.632
- Hamm?

14:10.675 --> 14:11.763
He was a patient here?

14:11.807 --> 14:12.939
- Originally.

14:12.982 --> 14:14.897
He came here for treatment
three years ago

14:14.941 --> 14:16.464
after he got out of prison,

14:16.507 --> 14:18.118
but he did so well
in the program

14:18.161 --> 14:21.382
that we made him an orderly
after he got sober.

14:21.425 --> 14:23.427
- You hired an ex-con
with addiction issues

14:23.471 --> 14:24.515
to work in your clinic?

14:24.559 --> 14:26.517
- Oh,
we don't judge people here.

14:26.561 --> 14:27.736
We help them.

14:27.779 --> 14:30.391
And Jeremy was a model employee
at first.

14:30.434 --> 14:33.829
But, uh...
- Then?

14:33.873 --> 14:36.919
- Jeremy started
to cross the line with Lillie,

14:36.963 --> 14:38.790
so we fired him.

14:38.834 --> 14:40.488
- Did Lillie's parents know
about this?

14:40.531 --> 14:42.533
- Oh, absolutely.
We told them what was going on

14:42.577 --> 14:45.014
and we asked them for help
with Lillie.

14:45.058 --> 14:47.060
- And they said
it wasn't Lillie's fault,

14:47.103 --> 14:48.409
it was ours.

14:48.452 --> 14:49.845
Then they pulled her
from the program,

14:49.889 --> 14:51.847
which we said was a mistake.

14:51.891 --> 14:53.675
- We need
to see Lillie's patient file.

14:53.718 --> 14:56.025
- Of course.

14:59.028 --> 15:00.943
- What an impressive campus
you have here.

15:00.987 --> 15:03.990
- We have some of the best
specialists in the field.

15:04.033 --> 15:05.992
Plus we're discreet.

15:06.035 --> 15:07.994
People pay a premium for that.

15:08.037 --> 15:10.518
- So how did Jeremy afford
to come here?

15:10.561 --> 15:12.563
- He was a scholarship patient.

15:12.607 --> 15:15.088
His fees were covered
by Covenant Church

15:15.131 --> 15:17.873
as part of their
addiction-outreach ministry.

15:17.917 --> 15:20.876
We provide
the physical healing.

15:20.920 --> 15:23.792
They provide the spiritual.

15:23.835 --> 15:25.446
[serene music]

15:25.489 --> 15:28.188
- We need to get back
to simpler times.

15:28.231 --> 15:30.494
To biblical times.

15:30.538 --> 15:32.627
We've been given the map
to salvation,

15:32.670 --> 15:36.065
but our woke culture
offends God

15:36.109 --> 15:39.808
and insults the very notion
of family.

15:39.851 --> 15:42.071
My brethren,
we've lost our way.

15:42.115 --> 15:44.421
But we mustn't lose our will.

15:44.465 --> 15:47.990
I'm here to lead you back,
to lead all of us back,

15:48.034 --> 15:50.688
to the glory
of the righteous man

15:50.732 --> 15:52.734
and his godly wife.
- [clears throat]

15:52.777 --> 15:54.214
Paster Bob is ready for you.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.825
He's asked his wife, Pat,
to join.

15:56.868 --> 15:59.871
♪

15:59.915 --> 16:04.659
- I don't know the young woman,
but...Jeremy?

16:04.702 --> 16:09.055
I'm just shocked and saddened.

16:09.098 --> 16:11.579
He was one
of our first success stories.

16:11.622 --> 16:12.754
- How so?

16:12.797 --> 16:14.799
- Oh,
he came to us from prison,

16:14.843 --> 16:17.193
strung out and hurting.

16:17.237 --> 16:19.021
We sent him over to the
good folks at Intentions.

16:19.065 --> 16:21.067
He got sober, found Jesus,

16:21.110 --> 16:25.506
and started walking the path
of the righteous man.

16:25.549 --> 16:28.248
Ken and Barb were so impressed

16:28.291 --> 16:30.641
they employed him
at their clinic.

16:30.685 --> 16:33.035
- Did you know that he was
recently fired from that job?

16:33.079 --> 16:34.602
- No.

16:34.645 --> 16:35.907
What for?

16:35.951 --> 16:37.518
- An inappropriate relationship
with Lillie.

16:37.561 --> 16:39.215
She was 17 and a patient there.

16:39.259 --> 16:42.871
- That is most unfortunate.

16:44.612 --> 16:46.048
- Was Jeremy a member here?

16:46.092 --> 16:49.008
- Technically, yes, but--

16:50.748 --> 16:52.011
- What she means is

16:52.054 --> 16:54.970
all of our children are
part of God's flock.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.581
Even the sinner
with a lustful heart.

16:57.625 --> 17:00.976
We haven't seen Jeremy
in quite some time.

17:01.020 --> 17:02.804
Now I think I know why.

17:02.847 --> 17:04.806
- So you don't know
where he is?

17:04.849 --> 17:06.634
Or where he might be going?

17:06.677 --> 17:09.637
- Physically, no.

17:09.680 --> 17:12.248
[sighs]
But spiritually--

17:12.292 --> 17:14.120
- I get it.

17:14.163 --> 17:17.993
He's gonna have a hard time
at the pearly gates.

17:18.037 --> 17:21.083
But to be honest, Bob...

17:21.127 --> 17:22.824
I probably will too.

17:22.867 --> 17:25.827
[soft tense music]

17:25.870 --> 17:28.656
♪

17:28.699 --> 17:32.181
[phone ringing]
- ♪ Praise the Lord

17:32.225 --> 17:33.922
- I apologize, gentlemen,

17:33.965 --> 17:36.098
but our men's group
starts at 4:30.

17:36.142 --> 17:38.318
I'm sorry I wasn't able
to be more helpful.

17:38.361 --> 17:40.320
But if there's anything else
you need from me

17:40.363 --> 17:42.800
or my ministry,
just let me know.

17:42.844 --> 17:44.237
Pat will show you out.

17:44.280 --> 17:48.328
♪

17:48.371 --> 17:50.330
- I don't like this, Jeremy.
I-I-I don't like this.

17:50.373 --> 17:51.722
I think
that we should get going.

17:51.766 --> 17:54.203
I think that staying here
is just a bad idea that--

17:54.247 --> 17:56.075
- Hey, Lillie.

17:56.118 --> 17:57.728
Calm down, okay?
We're safe here.

17:57.772 --> 17:59.687
- Safe?
You killed that man.

17:59.730 --> 18:00.992
Who was he?

18:01.036 --> 18:03.125
- He's just someone who
could hurt us, okay?

18:03.169 --> 18:05.693
It had to be done.
[door slams]

18:05.736 --> 18:07.695
- I don't like this.
We should go.

18:07.738 --> 18:10.872
[eerie music]

18:10.915 --> 18:11.916
- Pastor Bob?
What is he--?

18:11.960 --> 18:14.005
- Shh, no talking.

18:14.049 --> 18:17.139
Jeremy?
- She's pure.

18:17.183 --> 18:18.575
- What the hell is going on?

18:18.619 --> 18:19.794
- Well done.

18:19.837 --> 18:21.143
♪

18:21.187 --> 18:22.840
Faithful servant.

18:22.884 --> 18:24.842
♪

18:24.886 --> 18:27.715
You truly are the anointed one.

18:27.758 --> 18:29.891
- I'm getting outta here.

18:29.934 --> 18:32.676
- I'm afraid that's not going
to be happening.

18:32.720 --> 18:33.938
- What?

18:33.982 --> 18:35.592
- Get her ready.

18:35.636 --> 18:37.855
- Ready for what?

18:37.899 --> 18:39.944
Jeremy?

18:39.988 --> 18:41.163
- I'm sorry.

18:41.207 --> 18:43.252
♪

18:43.296 --> 18:44.775
[lock clicks]

18:44.819 --> 18:46.125
♪

18:50.912 --> 18:51.869
- So nothing on the BOLO?
- Uh-uh.

18:51.913 --> 18:53.175
Did you get the PI's file?

18:53.219 --> 18:55.090
- Yep, a copy's on the way.
He's old school.

18:55.134 --> 18:56.091
- Okay, what about the church?

18:56.135 --> 18:57.484
How'd that go?
- It was a bust.

18:57.527 --> 18:58.789
Bob Mitchell and his wife
didn't even know

18:58.833 --> 19:00.748
Jeremy was fired
from Intentions Rehab.

19:00.791 --> 19:02.184
No clue where he is now.

19:02.228 --> 19:03.577
- Never heard of Lillie either.

19:03.620 --> 19:05.535
- But who told you that?

19:05.579 --> 19:07.450
- Paster Bob did.
Why?

19:07.494 --> 19:09.191
- Lillie's patient file said

19:09.235 --> 19:12.281
her treatment included
spiritual counseling.

19:12.325 --> 19:14.718
Once a week,
led by Bob Mitchell.

19:14.762 --> 19:16.329
- So he lied about
not knowing Lillie.

19:16.372 --> 19:18.505
- So much
for not bearing false witness.

19:18.548 --> 19:19.549
- Right?

19:19.593 --> 19:20.855
- We going back?

19:20.898 --> 19:23.640
- Yeah, but let's switch it up
a little bit.

19:23.684 --> 19:25.207
Kristin and I will go.

19:25.251 --> 19:28.645
I'll be interested in your take
on this guy.

19:28.689 --> 19:31.387
- Wives, submit yourself
to your husbands.

19:31.431 --> 19:33.215
For the husband is the head
of the wife,

19:33.259 --> 19:35.435
as Christ is the head
of the church.

19:35.478 --> 19:38.438
As the church submits
to Christ, so also should...

19:38.481 --> 19:42.659
all: Wives submit to
their husbands in everything.

19:43.747 --> 19:45.923
Ladies, let's take a break.

19:45.967 --> 19:47.447
Shall we?

20:00.634 --> 20:03.245
Agent Scott, what's going on?

20:03.289 --> 20:07.684
- You are aware that lying
to the FBI is a crime, correct?

20:07.728 --> 20:09.295
- What do you mean, lying?

20:09.338 --> 20:12.428
- It's a verb,
meaning "to deceive."

20:12.472 --> 20:14.865
- Also a sin,
for what it's worth.

20:14.909 --> 20:16.824
- This is Agent Gaines.

20:16.867 --> 20:18.304
- I don't understand.

20:18.347 --> 20:19.827
- Lillie Jones?

20:19.870 --> 20:22.221
The girl your husband claimed
not to know?

20:22.264 --> 20:25.398
He counseled her when she was
a patient at Intentions.

20:25.441 --> 20:26.921
- He what?

20:26.964 --> 20:28.270
- No.

20:28.314 --> 20:29.619
There's been
a misunderstanding.

20:29.663 --> 20:30.794
I'll go get him.

20:30.838 --> 20:33.667
- Your receptionist says
he's not here.

20:33.710 --> 20:36.800
- He's supposed
to be leading the men's group.

20:36.844 --> 20:39.368
I'll call him.

20:39.412 --> 20:41.283
[line trills]

20:41.327 --> 20:42.806
- Hi, this is Pastor Bob.

20:42.850 --> 20:43.851
Please leave a message.

20:43.894 --> 20:45.331
Have a blessed day.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.289
- He in the habit
of turning off his phone

20:47.333 --> 20:48.856
in the middle of the day?

20:48.899 --> 20:51.772
- No, that's--
that's very strange.

20:51.815 --> 20:53.208
- Very strange.

20:53.252 --> 20:54.905
- You should give us
a call when you hear from him.

20:54.949 --> 20:59.823
♪

20:59.867 --> 21:01.782
She seemed genuinely spooked.

21:01.825 --> 21:03.653
- She should be.
Her husband lied to her.

21:03.697 --> 21:04.785
- Probably not the first time.

21:04.828 --> 21:06.265
The guy's hiding something.

21:06.308 --> 21:09.311
- 3:00.
Our friend from before.

21:09.355 --> 21:15.796
♪

21:15.839 --> 21:19.234
- Which agency?

21:19.278 --> 21:21.323
- Excuse me?

21:21.367 --> 21:26.894
- I'm guessing IRS,
given your undercover chops.

21:26.937 --> 21:28.852
- [laughs]
- I could see your wire.

21:28.896 --> 21:33.596
♪

21:33.640 --> 21:37.731
- Mel Montridge,
IRS Criminal Investigative.

21:37.774 --> 21:40.037
- What's Treasury want
with a church?

21:40.081 --> 21:41.909
- We're looking at Covenant
for tax fraud.

21:41.952 --> 21:44.564
♪

21:44.607 --> 21:47.349
- We'll show you ours
if you show us yours.

21:47.393 --> 21:49.612
C'mon, two federal agents
and an SSA walk

21:49.656 --> 21:51.353
into a women's bible study?

21:51.397 --> 21:54.791
Gotta be a joke
in their somewhere.

21:54.835 --> 21:56.097
Mel.

21:56.140 --> 21:59.056
I got four body drops
in the last 48 hours.

21:59.100 --> 22:00.667
I need your help.

22:00.710 --> 22:02.886
♪

22:02.930 --> 22:05.498
Please.

22:05.541 --> 22:07.935
- Weird to be out of this dress
and Spanx.

22:07.978 --> 22:09.719
Forgot how good it feels
to take a deep breath.

22:09.763 --> 22:10.851
- How long you been undercover?

22:10.894 --> 22:12.766
- Uh, on and off for a year,

22:12.809 --> 22:15.072
ever since my team started
investigating Bob Mitchell.

22:15.116 --> 22:16.552
- What prompted
the investigation?

22:16.596 --> 22:18.293
- A report was filed to the IRS

22:18.337 --> 22:21.905
alleging Covenant violated
its 501[c][3] status.

22:21.949 --> 22:23.907
- I got you.
- Oh.

22:23.951 --> 22:24.908
Thanks.

22:24.952 --> 22:26.693
- Violated how?

22:26.736 --> 22:29.696
- By stockpiling millions
of dollars in donations

22:29.739 --> 22:31.741
that were supposed to go
to philanthropic causes.

22:31.785 --> 22:33.177
- At Covenant,

22:33.221 --> 22:35.354
we're blessed to be able
to serve the community

22:35.397 --> 22:36.790
by spreading the gospel.

22:36.833 --> 22:39.836
From homeless shelters
to horse ranches to Haiti,

22:39.880 --> 22:42.578
the world is
our mission field.

22:42.622 --> 22:43.971
- How much of that is real?

22:44.014 --> 22:46.930
- The horse ranch exists,
minus the horses.

22:46.974 --> 22:49.629
It's an empty stone building
in the Jersey woods.

22:49.672 --> 22:50.934
- Do they do mission trips?

22:50.978 --> 22:53.589
- To beauty salons
in the tristate area maybe.

22:53.633 --> 22:55.417
The only money leaving
Covenant's accounts

22:55.461 --> 22:57.376
is spent on the leadership.

22:57.419 --> 23:00.901
- Bob's running
a for-profit church.

23:00.944 --> 23:02.424
Wish I thought of that.

23:02.468 --> 23:04.078
- Yeah, well,

23:04.121 --> 23:06.646
some members are tithing
at least 50% of their income.

23:06.689 --> 23:07.951
- Why though?

23:07.995 --> 23:11.694
- The more you give,
the closer you get to Bob.

23:11.738 --> 23:13.087
- Do you have a list
of those donors?

23:13.130 --> 23:14.958
- Yeah.

23:15.002 --> 23:17.961
These donors are
in the highest tier,

23:18.005 --> 23:18.962
the Chosen Circle.

23:19.006 --> 23:20.616
- Huh.
Can you stop there?

23:20.660 --> 23:23.053
Number four.
Ken and Barb Clymer.

23:23.097 --> 23:24.533
- The owners of Intentions

23:24.577 --> 23:26.535
are in the Chosen Circle
at Covenant.

23:26.579 --> 23:28.450
- Funny how
they left that part out.

23:28.494 --> 23:30.539
- It's not the only thing
they left out.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.759
Most clinics drug test
their patients,

23:32.802 --> 23:34.717
but Lillie's file didn't have
any results.

23:34.761 --> 23:36.458
- What,
they weren't testing her?

23:36.502 --> 23:37.981
- Or they didn't give us
the whole file,

23:38.025 --> 23:39.722
which led me to thinking
that maybe Jeremy

23:39.766 --> 23:41.768
was not the bad thing
that Dave was investigating

23:41.811 --> 23:43.465
at Intentions.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.467
And then I found this.

23:45.511 --> 23:48.470
- "Toxic Therapy:
When Healing Is Hell."

23:48.514 --> 23:49.645
- It's a blog

23:49.689 --> 23:51.865
written by a woman
named Aurora Beam.

23:51.908 --> 23:53.649
I found it when
I cross-referenced the list

23:53.693 --> 23:56.391
of patients from Intentions
with Dave's case file.

23:56.435 --> 23:57.871
- Her blog's about Intentions?

23:57.914 --> 24:00.395
- It's about
her being abused there.

24:00.439 --> 24:02.484
- The blog was
my therapist's suggestion.

24:02.528 --> 24:05.487
The more I write,
the smaller it gets.

24:05.531 --> 24:08.664
Like I can
wrap my arms around it.

24:08.708 --> 24:11.841
- Do you mind telling us what
happened to you at Intentions?

24:11.885 --> 24:15.410
- My parents sent me there
five years ago as a minor.

24:15.454 --> 24:18.500
Part of my treatment included
electroconvulsive therapy.

24:18.544 --> 24:20.067
- Shock therapy?

24:20.110 --> 24:21.634
Like in "Cuckoo's Nest?"

24:21.677 --> 24:24.506
- Same idea,
but a little less barbaric.

24:24.550 --> 24:27.509
Nowadays,
they put you under anesthesia.

24:27.553 --> 24:30.077
- Did something happen to you
while you were sedated?

24:32.253 --> 24:34.560
- I was raped.

24:34.603 --> 24:37.084
One day,
about a month into treatment,

24:37.127 --> 24:40.435
I woke up
to a man on top of me.

24:40.479 --> 24:41.741
I tried fighting back,

24:41.784 --> 24:45.048
but I was so groggy
I couldn't stop him.

24:45.092 --> 24:47.877
Next time,
he didn't bother sedating me.

24:47.921 --> 24:49.879
He knew I was powerless.

24:49.923 --> 24:51.838
Said I belonged to him.

24:51.881 --> 24:54.101
- Do you know who that man was?

24:54.144 --> 24:56.538
- Bob Mitchell.

24:56.582 --> 24:58.105
- The pastor
of the Covenant Church?

24:58.148 --> 25:00.194
- Oh, please.
That place isn't a church.

25:00.237 --> 25:01.717
It's a cult.

25:01.761 --> 25:04.067
The women are completely
submissive to their husbands.

25:04.111 --> 25:06.809
Like they're brainwashed.

25:06.853 --> 25:09.725
Do you know this man?

25:09.769 --> 25:12.685
- Jeremy.
We were inpatients together.

25:12.728 --> 25:14.121
- Did he ever get ECT?

25:14.164 --> 25:16.602
- Probably.
Most patients did.

25:16.645 --> 25:18.865
- We should
check Lillie's file.

25:18.908 --> 25:20.954
- I told my parents.

25:20.997 --> 25:24.087
But Bob denied it
and so did Intentions.

25:24.131 --> 25:27.047
They took their word over mine.

25:27.090 --> 25:29.484
Addicts lie, right?

25:29.528 --> 25:32.139
Who would believe me?

25:32.182 --> 25:34.010
- I believe you.

25:34.054 --> 25:36.578
♪

25:36.622 --> 25:37.579
Thank you.

25:37.623 --> 25:41.583
♪

25:41.627 --> 25:44.020
- Lillie's patient file said
she had ECT twice

25:44.064 --> 25:45.282
at Intentions--

25:45.326 --> 25:47.067
one two months ago,
another two weeks ago.

25:47.110 --> 25:49.765
- We've been looking at Lillie
as an accomplice.

25:49.809 --> 25:51.941
Maybe she's just a pawn
in all this.

25:51.985 --> 25:53.508
Where's Bob now?

25:53.552 --> 25:54.640
- Kristin said he's not
at the church.

25:54.683 --> 25:55.902
His phone's still turned off.

25:55.945 --> 25:57.599
- Get her and Ortiz out
to his house.

25:57.643 --> 26:00.689
Tell them we're right behind.

26:00.733 --> 26:01.951
- Kristin?

26:01.995 --> 26:03.213
Ortiz?

26:03.257 --> 26:04.780
- We're in the kitchen.

26:04.824 --> 26:07.783
[foreboding music]

26:07.827 --> 26:14.834
♪

26:22.319 --> 26:25.322
- Shooting's a new MO
for Jeremy.

26:25.366 --> 26:27.107
- Why waste time
stabbing his victims

26:27.150 --> 26:29.500
if he already had a gun?

26:29.544 --> 26:30.806
- Neighbor wasn't much help.

26:30.850 --> 26:32.416
Heard yelling,
didn't see anyone suspicious.

26:32.460 --> 26:33.504
- We get protection on Pat?

26:33.548 --> 26:35.376
- PD can't find her
at the church.

26:35.419 --> 26:38.161
She's not answering her cell,
and her car is gone.

26:38.205 --> 26:39.989
- Found these
in the bedroom safe.

26:42.165 --> 26:46.996
- 9 millimeter.
Bob was shot with his own gun.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.259
- Definitely not a suicide.

26:49.303 --> 26:50.652
- Anyone tamper with the safe?

26:50.696 --> 26:54.047
No. Whoever opened it
knew the code.

26:54.090 --> 26:55.701
- Had to be Pastor Pat.

26:55.744 --> 26:57.137
- Yeah, but why?

26:57.180 --> 26:58.486
- Maybe she found out about
the rapes.

26:58.529 --> 27:00.662
Decided to get revenge
on Bob herself.

27:00.706 --> 27:03.056
- Not very Christlike.
- Or practical.

27:03.099 --> 27:04.492
She knew that we
were suspicious of him,

27:04.535 --> 27:07.321
so why didn't she just
turn him in to us?

27:07.364 --> 27:09.671
- Have to be because she had
something to gain.

27:09.715 --> 27:11.194
- You think Pat's been
the woman behind the curtain

27:11.238 --> 27:13.196
this whole time?

27:13.240 --> 27:17.244
- I think if she is,
she picked the perfect spot.

27:17.287 --> 27:18.332
- Where is that?

27:18.375 --> 27:20.813
- In a cult
of submissive women.

27:20.856 --> 27:24.686
Hiding in plain sight.

27:24.730 --> 27:26.557
Right, Bob?

27:26.601 --> 27:27.689
- This might be chilly.

27:27.733 --> 27:30.518
- Who are you?
Where's Jeremy?

27:30.561 --> 27:33.739
- Don't waste another thought
on him, dear.

27:33.782 --> 27:36.132
Be still.

27:36.176 --> 27:40.702
They're all the same,
these men of ours.

27:40.746 --> 27:42.095
Weak.

27:42.138 --> 27:45.446
They know nothing of sacrifice,
pain,

27:45.489 --> 27:47.796
of creating life
where there was none.

27:47.840 --> 27:49.624
But you do.

27:49.668 --> 27:52.409
♪

27:52.453 --> 27:54.368
Congratulations.

27:54.411 --> 27:58.546
♪

27:58.589 --> 28:00.461
- I don't...

28:00.504 --> 28:02.202
I can't be pregnant.

28:02.245 --> 28:03.638
- I've been monitoring
your blood draws

28:03.682 --> 28:05.466
at Intentions weekly.

28:05.509 --> 28:08.556
I just had to be sure.

28:08.599 --> 28:09.688
Now we have proof.

28:09.731 --> 28:11.167
- But it's not possible.
I've never--

28:11.211 --> 28:12.734
Jeremy and I--
he wanted to wait.

28:12.778 --> 28:16.172
I--

28:16.216 --> 28:18.653
- You seriously
never questioned

28:18.697 --> 28:22.788
why a pastor was there
during your ECT?

28:22.831 --> 28:24.746
You can tell me.

28:24.790 --> 28:27.488
Deep down, you wanted
my husband, didn't you?

28:27.531 --> 28:31.579
♪

28:31.622 --> 28:32.754
- [gasps and whimpers]

28:32.798 --> 28:34.843
- Show some gratitude.

28:34.887 --> 28:37.890
Not everyone is given
such a blessing.

28:37.933 --> 28:41.328
Some of us have to take it
for ourselves.

28:41.371 --> 28:43.460
♪

28:43.504 --> 28:44.766
- What'd you find
on Pat Mitchell?

28:44.810 --> 28:46.594
- That her name's not
Pat Mitchell.

28:46.637 --> 28:48.335
She assumed a new identity
when she moved

28:48.378 --> 28:51.164
from Texas to New York
15 years ago.

28:51.207 --> 28:52.861
- Her real name's
Vivian Daniels.

28:52.905 --> 28:54.820
- Vivian the vitamin lady?

28:54.863 --> 28:56.473
- Ex-girlfriend of yours?

28:56.517 --> 28:59.476
- My aunt was a VitaJuvenate
consultant in the '90s.

28:59.520 --> 29:02.218
She worked her way up
to Trainer's Tier.

29:02.262 --> 29:03.872
- Was that English just now?

29:03.916 --> 29:06.266
- VitaJuvenate is
a wellness company

29:06.309 --> 29:07.876
founded by Pat as Vivian.

29:07.920 --> 29:09.704
Officially,
they sold supplements.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.837
- Yeah, Hana's right.
It was supplements,

29:11.880 --> 29:13.839
but they built their business
on recruitment.

29:13.882 --> 29:16.276
- So it was a pyramid scheme?

29:16.319 --> 29:18.365
- Yeah, according
to these lawsuits I found.

29:18.408 --> 29:19.714
- Well, it's pretty hard
to make a lawsuit work

29:19.758 --> 29:21.150
when your defendant disappears.

29:21.194 --> 29:22.543
- And then when the company
crumbled,

29:22.586 --> 29:23.892
my aunt was left
with a warehouse

29:23.936 --> 29:25.807
full of useless inventory.

29:25.851 --> 29:28.636
Meanwhile,
Pat fled with millions.

29:28.679 --> 29:29.811
- To start a cult?

29:29.855 --> 29:31.465
- Well, she didn't start it.

29:31.508 --> 29:33.162
Bob founded Covenant
in the '90s.

29:33.206 --> 29:34.381
But it wasn't until he met Pat

29:34.424 --> 29:35.817
that it financially started
taking off.

29:35.861 --> 29:38.472
- Pat recognized the value
in making Bob's message

29:38.515 --> 29:39.647
palatable to women.

29:39.690 --> 29:41.562
"Wives,
submit to your husbands"

29:41.605 --> 29:43.477
sounds of hell of a lot
less misogynistic coming out

29:43.520 --> 29:45.174
of a woman's mouth
than a man's.

29:45.218 --> 29:46.654
- So she became
a wolf in sheep's clothing

29:46.697 --> 29:47.960
and started the grift
all over again.

29:48.003 --> 29:49.309
- Only instead of vitamins,

29:49.352 --> 29:50.440
now she's selling
"the good ol' days."

29:50.484 --> 29:51.572
[phone ringing]
- Hm.

29:51.615 --> 29:52.747
Gaines.

29:52.791 --> 29:54.705
- It's the financial part
that's genius.

29:54.749 --> 29:56.838
The scam is baked
into the cult's ideology.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.231
- The donors make the money,

29:58.274 --> 29:59.928
which then they tithe
to Covenant.

29:59.972 --> 30:02.191
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

30:02.235 --> 30:03.453
Brooklyn PD just got a call.

30:03.497 --> 30:04.803
Shooting at Intentions Rehab.

30:04.846 --> 30:06.674
- Kristin, with me.

30:06.717 --> 30:08.589
[dramatic music]

30:08.632 --> 30:10.809
- He was aiming for my heart.

30:10.852 --> 30:11.984
- Who was?
- [sobs]

30:12.027 --> 30:13.376
Ken.

30:13.420 --> 30:16.553
He said it was time,
that Bob called the Journey.

30:16.597 --> 30:17.598
- What journey?

30:17.641 --> 30:18.686
- To where it ends.

30:18.729 --> 30:19.774
- The world?

30:19.818 --> 30:21.515
- It's only
for the Chosen Circle.

30:21.558 --> 30:23.778
The chance to discard
our bodily shells

30:23.822 --> 30:25.127
to achieve salvation.

30:25.171 --> 30:28.304
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Slow down, slow down.

30:28.348 --> 30:29.915
If Ken booked a ticket
to the end of the world,

30:29.958 --> 30:31.525
why didn't you go with him?

30:31.568 --> 30:33.483
- 'Cause this morning
I found this.

30:33.527 --> 30:35.572
♪

30:35.616 --> 30:38.967
- It's the missing blood test
from Lillie's file.

30:39.011 --> 30:40.882
She's pregnant.

30:40.926 --> 30:43.885
- The Prophecy requires
the marriage of a virgin

30:43.929 --> 30:45.278
to the anointed one.

30:45.321 --> 30:47.584
When Ken said it was time,
that it was Lillie,

30:47.628 --> 30:48.890
I knew it couldn't be true.

30:48.934 --> 30:50.936
I tried to convince Ken.

30:50.979 --> 30:52.546
I showed him
Lillie's pregnancy results,

30:52.589 --> 30:53.721
but he wouldn't believe me.

30:53.764 --> 30:56.245
- Okay, Barb.
I need you to calm down

30:56.289 --> 30:59.422
and tell me where did Ken go?

30:59.466 --> 31:02.034
- To the marriage supper
of the lamb.

31:02.077 --> 31:04.906
Revelation says,
"For the wedding of the lamb

31:04.950 --> 31:07.735
has come, and his bride has
made herself ready."

31:07.778 --> 31:12.261
♪

31:12.305 --> 31:13.741
- The pill dispenser's been
cleaned out.

31:13.784 --> 31:15.047
The system says

31:15.090 --> 31:17.745
100,000 milligrams
of phenobarbital's missing.

31:17.788 --> 31:19.747
- A marriage between
a virginal bride

31:19.790 --> 31:21.444
and an anointed lamb.

31:21.488 --> 31:23.403
♪

31:23.446 --> 31:26.667
It's Lillie
and Jeremy's wedding.

31:26.710 --> 31:28.756
A Phenobarbital feast.

31:28.799 --> 31:31.933
Bob's followers are planning
a mass suicide.

31:37.156 --> 31:39.985
- Toll cams caught Ken
going south on I-95.

31:40.028 --> 31:42.465
- Which is where we're headed.
We're gonna need specifics.

31:42.509 --> 31:43.989
- The Covenant owns a ton
of property.

31:44.032 --> 31:45.512
I'm trying to narrow it down.

31:45.555 --> 31:47.514
- Pat had everyone
under her thumb,

31:47.557 --> 31:51.257
parishioners, Jeremy, Bob,
just like with VitaJuvenate.

31:51.300 --> 31:52.998
But the walls were closing in,

31:53.041 --> 31:55.957
so Pat has Jeremy kill everyone
who could expose her.

31:56.001 --> 31:57.828
- Including convincing
her followers

31:57.872 --> 31:58.917
to kill themselves.

31:58.960 --> 32:00.005
- Mm,
the power of brainwashing.

32:00.048 --> 32:01.006
To them, it's not death.

32:01.049 --> 32:03.008
It's the promise
of eternal life.

32:03.051 --> 32:04.879
- But she learned
from her past mistakes.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.229
This time, there'll be
no witnesses to her grift.

32:07.273 --> 32:08.796
No one left alive to sue her.

32:08.839 --> 32:11.233
- What verse did Barb cite
for Pat's prophecy?

32:11.277 --> 32:12.539
- Something from Revelation.

32:12.582 --> 32:14.236
- I got it.
- What?

32:14.280 --> 32:16.543
- The horse ranch in Jersey,
the one Mel told us about?

32:16.586 --> 32:20.068
It's owned by a shell corp
called Rev197.

32:20.112 --> 32:21.809
- Call Ortiz
and Jersey State Police.

32:21.852 --> 32:23.071
Tell them to hurry.

32:23.115 --> 32:25.073
[engine revving]

32:25.117 --> 32:26.988
♪

32:27.032 --> 32:29.860
[ominous music]

32:29.904 --> 32:31.079
♪

32:31.123 --> 32:33.255
- As the Prophecy foretold,

32:33.299 --> 32:35.431
our Journey
from this earthly plane

32:35.475 --> 32:38.957
begins with
this sacred marriage covenant.

32:39.000 --> 32:42.090
Faithful ones,
our time has come

32:42.134 --> 32:44.440
to ascend to eternal life.

32:44.484 --> 32:48.401
The preparation of the blood
and the wedding of the chosen.

32:48.444 --> 32:50.577
all:
The preparation of the blood

32:50.620 --> 32:52.318
and the wedding of the chosen.

32:52.361 --> 32:54.015
- FBI!
Hands in the air!

32:54.059 --> 32:55.364
Right now.

32:55.408 --> 32:56.452
- Where is she?

32:56.496 --> 32:58.280
Where's Pat?
- She's with Bob.

32:58.324 --> 33:01.109
- He called the Prophecy
and the journey has begun.

33:01.153 --> 33:02.502
- I don't think so, pal.

33:02.545 --> 33:05.070
Bob's dead.
[person gasps]

33:05.113 --> 33:06.158
- Don't listen to him.

33:06.201 --> 33:08.508
Bob warned us
of a false prophet.

33:08.551 --> 33:10.379
[glass shatters]

33:10.423 --> 33:12.468
- Nobody's drinking
any wine cooler today.

33:12.512 --> 33:14.296
Back away from the table.

33:14.340 --> 33:15.558
I said back up!

33:15.602 --> 33:18.866
♪

33:18.909 --> 33:23.349
Listen, I know what it's like
to believe in something,

33:23.392 --> 33:25.351
to need it so bad.

33:25.394 --> 33:28.006
I felt the same way when
my brother died.

33:28.049 --> 33:31.574
But I'm telling you right now,
this isn't it.

33:31.618 --> 33:34.273
Bob is dead
because Pat killed him.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.057
And your chosen one
is an ex-con

33:36.101 --> 33:37.580
currently wanted
for four murders.

33:37.624 --> 33:39.060
And the bride who's supposed
to kick this whole

33:39.104 --> 33:40.627
highway-to-heaven off?

33:40.670 --> 33:43.934
Well, how can I put this
without ruffling your feathers?

33:43.978 --> 33:46.372
Your virgin's knocked up.

33:46.415 --> 33:48.026
So where's Pat?

33:48.069 --> 33:49.897
- Bob and Pat are
with the bride

33:49.940 --> 33:52.943
and the anointed one now
in the Chamber.

33:52.987 --> 33:54.249
- You mean the storage room?

33:54.293 --> 33:56.251
- The Chamber!

33:56.295 --> 33:57.426
- No Pat, no Lillie.

33:57.470 --> 33:58.949
Jeremy's in there
dead on the floor.

33:58.993 --> 34:01.909
Shot in the head.
[cultists gasping]

34:01.952 --> 34:03.476
♪

34:03.519 --> 34:05.173
- He's lying.

34:05.217 --> 34:06.957
The Prophecy is real!

34:07.001 --> 34:08.220
The--
- Ken.

34:08.263 --> 34:09.482
I'm gonna ask you
once last time.

34:09.525 --> 34:12.659
Where's Pat?
And where did she take Lillie?

34:12.702 --> 34:14.443
- I don't know.

34:14.487 --> 34:16.402
We thought they were in there.

34:16.445 --> 34:23.452
♪

34:26.455 --> 34:29.415
[suspenseful music]

34:29.458 --> 34:34.463
♪

34:34.507 --> 34:36.161
- FBI!
Stop right there!

34:36.204 --> 34:39.077
- Hello, Vivian.
I'll take that.

34:39.120 --> 34:42.210
[sirens wailing]

34:42.254 --> 34:44.082
♪

34:44.125 --> 34:45.996
- Get your hands off me.

34:46.040 --> 34:47.563
♪

34:47.607 --> 34:49.087
- FBI!

34:49.130 --> 34:52.090
It's okay, it's okay.
Is anybody else here?

34:52.133 --> 34:54.570
♪

34:54.614 --> 34:56.746
- I got her.

34:56.790 --> 34:58.574
Clear!

34:58.618 --> 35:05.625
♪

35:06.147 --> 35:07.105
- Lillie.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.194
[indistinct radio chatter]

35:09.237 --> 35:16.070
♪

35:20.161 --> 35:22.120
- Where are they taking her?

35:22.163 --> 35:23.599
Where are they taking my baby?

35:23.643 --> 35:25.601
- Your baby?
[laughs]

35:25.645 --> 35:27.255
That's a good one, Viv.

35:27.299 --> 35:29.301
You know, I'm curious.

35:29.344 --> 35:32.565
The gospel according
to, well, you,

35:32.608 --> 35:35.045
says a woman's sole job

35:35.089 --> 35:38.527
is to bear her husband's child.

35:38.571 --> 35:40.225
So why didn't you ever
have kids?

35:40.268 --> 35:42.575
♪

35:42.618 --> 35:45.578
It's because you can't, right?
That's sad.

35:45.621 --> 35:47.145
I'll give you that.

35:47.188 --> 35:49.625
But you can't blame yourself.

35:49.669 --> 35:52.541
It's not yourfault.

35:52.585 --> 35:55.718
But you know
what is your fault?

35:55.762 --> 35:57.633
Everything else.

35:57.677 --> 35:59.244
You could tolerate
Bob pretending

35:59.287 --> 36:00.462
to run the church you built,

36:00.506 --> 36:01.811
you could even stomach

36:01.855 --> 36:03.683
all of the other
horrible things he was doing,

36:03.726 --> 36:07.382
but when he gave another woman
a baby?

36:07.426 --> 36:08.644
[scoffs]

36:08.688 --> 36:11.778
Oh,
that's when you lost your mind.

36:11.821 --> 36:13.736
♪

36:13.780 --> 36:16.826
But you know
what I can't figure out?

36:16.870 --> 36:20.482
What was the plan
in all of this?

36:20.526 --> 36:23.268
Hide out with Lillie
till she gave birth?

36:23.311 --> 36:27.315
Then kill her and start
a new con as a doting mother?

36:27.359 --> 36:29.187
- I was saving them.

36:29.230 --> 36:31.319
- Oh, please.
You were saving yourself.

36:31.363 --> 36:34.714
You just couldn't leave
without the money.

36:34.757 --> 36:36.455
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

36:36.498 --> 36:38.108
- Viv.

36:38.152 --> 36:41.503
You forced Bob
to wire the church's money

36:41.547 --> 36:44.376
to a Sally Sullivan.

36:44.419 --> 36:48.162
Then you used that same name
to rent a car,

36:48.206 --> 36:50.208
which was really dumb.

36:50.251 --> 36:51.426
You should've gone
with a clunker.

36:51.470 --> 36:55.169
These SUVs,
they all have GPS now.

36:55.213 --> 36:57.389
Led us right to you.

36:57.432 --> 37:04.439
♪

37:10.445 --> 37:12.360
Sally Sullivan.

37:12.404 --> 37:15.320
♪

37:15.363 --> 37:19.454
I bet it was expensive
to look this cheap.

37:19.498 --> 37:21.369
♪

37:21.413 --> 37:24.503
[cuffs jingling]

37:24.546 --> 37:26.766
- [grunts]

37:26.809 --> 37:28.420
- Good luck in prison.

37:28.463 --> 37:29.725
[cuffs clicking]

37:29.769 --> 37:33.251
Plenty of souls to save there.

37:33.294 --> 37:35.383
Right, Pastor?

37:35.427 --> 37:42.434
♪

37:53.706 --> 37:55.447
- Yes! Take that.
- All right.

37:55.490 --> 37:56.926
Hana's on fire, okay.

37:56.970 --> 37:58.580
But it ain't over
until it's over.

37:58.624 --> 38:00.234
Check this out, people.

38:00.278 --> 38:01.409
all: Oh!

38:01.453 --> 38:05.152
- [laughing] Oh.
I told you.

38:05.195 --> 38:06.849
- More drinks?
- Sure.

38:06.893 --> 38:08.721
- As far as buy-ins go,
this is great.

38:08.764 --> 38:10.331
[laughter]
- Weapons and alcohol.

38:10.375 --> 38:12.420
What could possibly go wrong?
[laughter]

38:12.464 --> 38:13.508
Oh, another round here,
please.

38:13.552 --> 38:15.902
Thanks.
- You got it.

38:15.945 --> 38:18.470
- All right, question for you.

38:18.513 --> 38:19.732
Your brother.

38:19.775 --> 38:21.429
- What about him?

38:21.473 --> 38:23.736
- Can I ask?

38:23.779 --> 38:26.608
- Oh, I just assumed

38:26.652 --> 38:29.394
when you guys were
vetting me the other day,

38:29.437 --> 38:31.526
somebody told you.

38:31.570 --> 38:33.702
- No.

38:33.746 --> 38:35.443
No, but if it's not something
you wanna--

38:35.487 --> 38:36.662
- No, I don't mind.

38:36.705 --> 38:39.360
I, uh...

38:39.404 --> 38:42.320
I like talking about him.

38:42.363 --> 38:43.886
His name was Mikey.

38:43.930 --> 38:46.324
And he was the baby
of the family.

38:46.367 --> 38:49.414
Smart, funny, the shining star.

38:49.457 --> 38:50.719
[melancholic music]

38:50.763 --> 38:53.200
Senior year of high school,
he's 18 years old

38:53.243 --> 38:56.377
and headed to Syracuse
on a baseball scholarship.

38:56.421 --> 38:59.293
He goes down to Florida
on spring break

38:59.337 --> 39:00.860
with his buddies.

39:00.903 --> 39:02.383
They go to a bar.

39:02.427 --> 39:04.211
His buddies lose track of him

39:04.254 --> 39:08.650
and he doesn't go back
to the hotel that night.

39:08.694 --> 39:12.350
So eventually, I call the cops.

39:12.393 --> 39:14.787
My parents are freaking out.

39:14.830 --> 39:17.529
They hop the first flight
to Miami.

39:17.572 --> 39:20.358
And 3:00 that afternoon,

39:20.401 --> 39:23.970
Fort Lauderdale PD bring
in a guy for questioning.

39:24.013 --> 39:25.841
Larry Michael Davis.

39:25.885 --> 39:28.017
Transient, criminal record.

39:28.061 --> 39:32.370
He had been seen hassling Mikey
outside the bar that night.

39:32.413 --> 39:33.893
- Mm, did they arrest him?

39:33.936 --> 39:35.634
- No.

39:35.677 --> 39:37.549
Detectives let him go.

39:37.592 --> 39:39.420
Said they didn't have enough
to hold him.

39:39.464 --> 39:40.595
- Mm.

39:40.639 --> 39:45.470
- Couple hours later,
PD find Mikey...

39:45.513 --> 39:49.299
dead in Davis' tent.

39:49.343 --> 39:50.388
Stabbed three times.

39:50.431 --> 39:52.390
His wallet and watch were
missing.

39:52.433 --> 39:54.566
They tried to tell us
that he had been dead

39:54.609 --> 39:56.568
since the night before,
